    "methodology": "GUS BSW is the Polish edition of the EU Structure of Earnings Survey, coordinated with Eurostat. ISCO-08 codes. Covers enterprises with 10+ employees. Values converted from PLN to EUR at 2022 average rate (1 EUR = 4.70 PLN) and stored as EUR equivalents for cross-country comparison. Updated to 2024 via GUS annual wage survey. PLN nominal growth +25% (2022-2024) plus PLN appreciation vs EUR (4.70\u21924.30). Net EUR equivalent: +36.6%. Poland saw the highest wage growth in the EU over this period.",
    "coverage": "Poland national. Warsaw derived from GUS regional data for Wojew\u00f3dztwo Mazowieckie (~20% above national median for professional roles).",
    "limitations": "EUR values are converted from PLN at 2022 average rate. Actual EUR equivalent will vary by exchange rate. ISCO codes map to broad groups. Poland salaries are significantly below Western European averages; figures reflect the domestic market.",
    "ingestion_mode": "import",
    "ingested_at": "2026-03-28",
    "notes": "All values EUR-equivalent converted from PLN (2022 avg: 4.70 PLN/EUR). Gross annual salary. Full-time employees."
